        "bodies":["Paris, France\r\nSept - Dec\r\n\r\nLaurent is a vital figure within the Île-de-France growing community, which was once home to the country’s strongest tradition of market gardens. Where most land has been sold off for development, Laurent is holding on to a five-generation strong dedication to seeds, soil and flavour. Each of his 160 varieties is typical of the region and grown from his own saved seeds, therefore naturally adapted to his soil. Less earthy in flavour than red or black, his White Beetroot grow without any chemical intervention, which you can tell from their tender, thin-skinned form.","","","","","","","","","",""],"imageRatios":["S","S","S","S","S","S","S","S","S","S","S"],
